                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/594: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-19T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Department’s telegram 51 August 15 [<hi rend="italic">18</hi>], 2 p.m. Upon
                    arrival of Director Jaquith Near East Relief I suggested to him that he
                    [apparent omission] conversation with the Minister for Foreign Affairs reported
                    in my cipher telegram 117, August 7, 6 p.m. Jaquith informed me yesterday he has
                    made an arrangement very much as reported in my 117, August 7, 6 p.m. and that
                    he understood two Greek vessels with some of the refugees aboard have already
                    left Constantinople for Saloniki.</p>
                <p>I understand League of Nations will care for some 5,000 of these refugees in
                    [Thrace?]. Constantinople informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
